20/11/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- US Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defence for European and NATO affairs Ian Brzezinski addressed a regional defence forum in Zagreb on Wednesday (19 November) and urged the Southeastern Europe Brigade (SEEBRIG) to prepare for possible deployment outside the region.
SEEBRIG was established to participate in peacekeeping and humanitarian operations under the command of NATO and the EU, and under a mandate of the UN and the OSCE.
As for Croatia's parliamentary elections this Sunday, the OSCE's Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights (ODIHR) says it will issue preliminary results Monday.
Canada's Ian Mitchell heads the ODIHR election observation mission.
(HINA, BBC, OSCE Web site, HINA, BBC - 19/11/03)
